    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.44"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">106. Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">44</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ALVIN KNODEL, PRINCIPLE
                        
                    V. SPENGLER, DEPT. VOC. AGRICULTURE</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">Elgin Public Schools</hi> 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">FULLY ACCREDITED STATE HIGH SCHOOL
                        <lb/>
                    BARTON THOMPSON</hi>, Supt.
                        <lb/>
                    
                    Directors:
                        <hi rend="caps">M. E. WITTMER PRESIDENT
                            <lb/>
                        AUGUST ESLINGER
                            <lb/>
                        EMIL FROEMMING
                            <lb/>
                        ERVIN DACHTLER
                            <lb/>
                        ELMER BENDER
                            <lb/>
                    
                    ARNOLD MEYER, TREASURER 
                        <lb/>
                    R. E. BENDER, CLERK</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">Elgin, No. Dak.</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>February 3, 1959</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Department of English</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>On behalf of Carol Eslinger and the Sophomore Class of Elgin High School I wish to thank you for your kind letter of some weeks past.</p>
                
                <p>We certainly had a sucessful Frontier Unit study based on your <hi rend="underline">Song of Three Friends</hi> and <hi rend="underline">Song of Hugh Glass.</hi> Unofrtunately, our meager little library does not have the complete cycle. I have tried to find your books listed in various library catalogs and so far haven't found them. I do hope to order them as I feel they are basic literature for young people, and particularly for this section of the country.</p>
                
                <p>I believe that many of the students were impressed by the fact that "a real live author" was approachable and took an interest in them. If I could just stimulate the reading habit in my students it would be a great accomplishment.</p>
                
                <p>Perhaps you would like to have this clipping from our weekly newspaper.</p>
                
                <p>Way back in the 1920's my English teacher inspired us with your works, since then I have"exposed" my students to them also, I hope some of it "took".</p>
                
                <p>Personally, I am greatly interested in history of the <del>w</del><add>W</add>est, and particularly of this Dakota section. I have done some writing on this level and am presently the president of the Medora Branch of the League of American Pen Women. S veral years ago I wrote and edited the 75th anniversary booklet of Dickinson, <hi rend="caps">N.D.</hi> I was also the editor and writer of 95% of the 127 page diamond jubilee issue of <hi rend="caps">THE DICKINSON PRESS</hi>. I Feel strongly that too many people do not appreciate their heritage and much historical data is neglected and lost.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes to you from the class and myself, I am,</salute>
                
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Margaret Anderson  Stav, Eng.Inst.</signed>
                
                    <signed>Margaret Anderson 
                    Stav</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
